Description: Blue-green faience amulet showing an Aegis with the goddess Hathor, rough surface. Above the sun disc and below the collar a horizontal perforation, both broken in the middle. The rear is flat and smooth.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.14, upper level
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 160)
